title: Congratulating the Wantagh High School Girls Volleyball Team upon the occasion of winning the 2010 Long Island Class A Championship
fulltext:
LEGISLATIVE  RESOLUTION  congratulating  the  Wantagh  High School Girls
Volleyball Team and Coach Katie McKeefrey upon the occasion  of  winning
the 2010 Long Island Class A Championship

WHEREAS,  Excellence  and  success in competitive sports can be achieved
only through strenuous practice, team play and team spirit, nurtured  by
dedicated coaching and strategic planning; and
  WHEREAS, Athletic competition enhances the moral and physical develop-
ment of the young people of this State, preparing them for the future by
instilling  in  them  the  value  of teamwork, encouraging a standard of
healthy living, imparting a desire for success and developing a sense of
fair play and competition; and
  WHEREAS, The Wantagh High School Girls Volleyball Team  are  the  2010
Long Island Class A Champions; outlasting a five-game set with Bellport,
the  Lady  Warriors  won  with  scores of 25-23, 22-25, 25-10, 8-25, and
25-22 securing the Class A title; and
  WHEREAS, The athletic talent displayed by this team is  due  in  great
part  to  the  efforts  of Coach Katie McKeefrey, a skilled and inspira-
tional tutor, respected for her ability to develop potential into excel-
lence; and
  WHEREAS, The team's  overall  record  is  outstanding,  and  the  team
members  were  loyally  and  enthusiastically supported by family, fans,
friends and the community at large; and
  WHEREAS, The hallmarks of the Wantagh  High  School  Girls  Volleyball
Team,  from the opening game of the season to participation in the cham-
pionship, were a sisterhood of athletic ability, of good  sportsmanship,
of  honor  and of scholarship, demonstrating that these team players are
second to none; and
  WHEREAS, Athletically and academically, the team members  have  proven
themselves to be an unbeatable combination of talents, reflecting favor-
ably on their school; and
  WHEREAS, Coach Katie McKeefrey has done a superb job in guiding, mold-
ing and inspiring the team members toward their goals; and
  WHEREAS, Sports competition instills the values of teamwork, pride and
accomplishment,  and  Coach Katie McKeefrey and the outstanding athletes
on the Wantagh High School Girls Volleyball Team  have  clearly  made  a
contribution  to  the spirit of excellence which is a tradition of their
school; now, therefore, be it
  RESOLVED, That this Legislative Body pause  in  its  deliberations  to
congratulate the Wantagh High School Girls Volleyball Team; its members:
Cristina  Bush,  Nicole  Kelly, Jenny Ilibassi, Jenna Greenberg, Loretta
O'Brien, Carly Simeone, Lauren Pennino, Carissa Gagliardi, Jenn  Lipski,
Anna  Paulik,  Gerri  Sciolto,  Shannon  Kerley,  Nicole Simeone, Chesea
Greenberg, Kimberly Drexler, Jillian Motschwiller, and  Christina  Ellul
and  Coaches  Katie  McKeefrey  and  Jaymie  Tauber on their outstanding
season and overall team record; and be it further
  RESOLVED, That copies of this Resolution, suitably engrossed, be tran-
smitted to the Wantagh High School Girls  Volleyball  Team  and  to  the
aforementioned coaches.
actClause: LEGISLATIVE RESOLUTION congratulating the Wantagh High School Girls Volleyball Team and Coach Katie McKeefrey upon the occasion of winning the 2010 Long Island Class A Championship
